 State Variables

Definition: Variables whose values are stored on the blockchain.

Scope: Accessible by all functions in the contract.

Persistence: Values remain on the blockchain until updated.

Declaration: Declared outside functions in the contract.

Example:
//SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT

pragma solidity ^0.8.0;

contract demo { 

    string public name;
        uint public class;
    function setAge () public {
    class = 10;
    name= "harshita";
    }
    
}
  
